WEBVTT

00:14.722 --> 00:21.574
Welcome to the Petty Profit Podcast, where we talk about news, culture, and politics from a Christian worldview.

00:21.774 --> 00:23.196
I am your host Joel Berry.

00:23.837 --> 00:26.782
I am glad to be with you, and I am glad you are listening.

00:27.223 --> 00:29.567
If you like the show, don't forget to review us on iTunes.

00:29.587 --> 00:33.714
You can also reach out to me at contact at thepetyprofit.com.

00:34.178 --> 00:38.124
or you can reach us on our website, www.thepettiprofit.com.

00:38.164 --> 00:44.893
You can find all kinds of good stuff there, articles and satire that you won't hear on the podcast, as well as a contact form.

00:44.933 --> 00:48.458
You can get ahold of me on that contact form.

00:48.578 --> 00:49.820
So be sure to reach out.

00:49.960 --> 00:50.801
We'd love to hear from you.

00:51.983 --> 01:02.578
And this week, just quickly, I want to talk about what is going on, what in the world is going on in the streets right now, all these statues being torn down.

01:02.754 --> 01:10.424
you know, luckily I live in a relatively boring part of the country called Toledo, Ohio where, you know, we saw a little bit of rioting.

01:10.564 --> 01:17.513
It was minimal, not much, but I am seeing what is going on on the news in major cities all across the country.

01:17.533 --> 01:19.295
And it's really, it's, it's tragic.

01:19.395 --> 01:24.361
It's sad to see all the destruction and just the hatred and the unrest.

01:26.344 --> 01:31.250
But today I want to talk about what's happening in particular with this,

01:31.554 --> 01:33.737
push to remove statues.

01:34.478 --> 01:36.600
And more broadly, I suppose, to remove symbols.

01:37.502 --> 01:47.454
We've seen this happen a lot when there is a national tragedy, a shooting, an instance of police brutality, something that shocks the conscience of our nation.

01:47.835 --> 01:52.941
Seems like our go-to response lately has been to remove statues, to ban flags.

01:53.842 --> 01:55.525
And you might wonder, what's driving that?

01:55.565 --> 01:59.730
And I think that many people have different opinions on that.

02:00.194 --> 02:02.977
I wanted to explore that a little bit in this episode.

02:03.698 --> 02:07.163
And to give it context, we are going to travel way back in time.

02:07.964 --> 02:09.185
A long, long time ago.

02:09.466 --> 02:12.309
I'm talking over 5,000 years ago.

02:17.716 --> 02:24.264
In the country of Syria, about a 30-minute drive from the city of Aleppo, lie the ruins of Elba.

02:24.845 --> 02:29.170
You certainly can't tell by the barely recognizable piles of stone today, but

02:29.602 --> 02:33.428
Elba was once one of the greatest kingdoms on Earth.

02:34.891 --> 02:42.002
In fact, it was the first recorded world power equal to Egypt, in might and influence.

02:42.022 --> 02:56.786
It started as a small settlement around 3500 BC, about 1,500 years before the birth of Abraham, and it stood proudly for over 1,000 years before being burned to the ground.

02:59.714 --> 03:09.730
Over 4,000 years after the destruction of Elba, in 1974, archaeologists made an amazing discovery while excavating the city.

03:10.371 --> 03:15.419
Neatly stored in two small rooms that branched off from a large audience hall.

03:16.080 --> 03:27.058
Clay tablets, perfectly baked and preserved by the fire that destroyed the city, gave us insight into a civilization that had been lost for millennia.

03:27.490 --> 03:37.202
Many of the tablets turned out to be simple ledgers for recording inventories and economic data, but some of them turned out to be much more interesting.

03:37.963 --> 03:45.572
One tablet describes an oddly familiar ritual used for purification on the day of a king's wedding.

03:46.173 --> 03:51.860
In this ritual, a female goat is adorned with a silver bracelet around its neck.

03:51.880 --> 03:56.626
The evils of that community are then ceremonially transferred to the goat

03:56.994 --> 03:59.237
and it is cast out into the wilderness.

04:00.097 --> 04:01.399
Does that sound a little familiar?

04:02.020 --> 04:02.740
Well, let's try this.

04:03.461 --> 04:07.566
Fast forward about a thousand years after those ancient tablets were written.

04:07.986 --> 04:14.974
Twelve tribes of recently freed slaves called the Israelites have escaped Egypt led by a man named Moses.

04:16.176 --> 04:25.426
It is here that the God of Abraham reveals himself to these people, to Abraham's descendants in the wilderness.

04:25.890 --> 04:34.463
In this revelation, we get the law of Moses, and we see the second recorded instance of this strange ritual with the goats.

04:35.365 --> 04:36.927
But this time it's a bit different.

04:37.608 --> 04:43.518
The ambiguous idea of evil mentioned in the old Elbin tablets now has a name.

04:44.239 --> 04:47.524
It's called sin, which means to miss the mark.

04:48.646 --> 04:54.034
The mark is God's newly recorded and revealed mosaic law.

04:54.338 --> 04:56.140
an impossible standard of holiness.

04:56.921 --> 04:59.763
Everyone at some point in their lives will be guilty of sin.

05:00.484 --> 05:03.928
That sin has a price, and it must be atoned for.

05:03.968 --> 05:07.791
In this ancient ritual, there are two goats, not one.

05:08.272 --> 05:10.494
And instead of female goats, they were male goats.

05:11.215 --> 05:14.058
The first goat is killed as an offering to God.

05:15.079 --> 05:20.464
Its blood is sprinkled on the altar of the tabernacle to cover the sins of the people.

05:21.305 --> 05:22.386
And the second goat

05:22.722 --> 05:25.104
becomes what we now call the scapegoat.

05:25.905 --> 05:37.056
Moses recorded this ritual in the book of Leviticus when he said, the priest shall lay both his hands upon the head of the live goat and confess over it all the iniquities and transgressions of the Israelites.

05:38.077 --> 05:51.730
Whatever their sins, putting them on the head of the goat, and it shall be sent off to Azazaeo, which means the inaccessible place or the barren wilderness or put much more simply

05:52.450 --> 05:52.911
to hell.

05:53.532 --> 05:59.841
In that word, Azazel, Hebrew speaking people in Israel still use that word today.

05:59.881 --> 06:06.070
And if you hear someone say it, direct it at you, well, they're telling you to go to hell.

06:06.952 --> 06:15.184
But even ancient pagans practiced some form of this ritual during festivals or to avert disasters like drought or pestilence.

06:15.925 --> 06:17.908
And their version was much crueler.

06:18.509 --> 06:19.551
They didn't use goats.

06:20.372 --> 06:21.714
They used human beings.

06:22.306 --> 06:26.732
usually a reject of society, someone who is poor or homeless or crippled.

06:27.914 --> 06:37.968
They would dress that person in fine clothes, allow this person to feast, ceremonially transfer their evil onto him, and then cast him out of the city.

06:38.588 --> 06:43.175
In worse or more desperate cases, they would kill this person first.

06:44.517 --> 06:51.346
The theme I see all through these cultures, separated by thousands of years, is this idea of guilt.

06:51.842 --> 06:56.109
At some level, every human being knows he isn't alright.

06:56.690 --> 06:57.892
We aren't alright.

06:59.254 --> 07:09.492
As image bearers of God the Creator, we all share the same moral conscience whether we are a protester in Portland or a king in the ancient kingdom of Elba.

07:10.313 --> 07:18.066
And although many cultures have come up with different answers and explanations for that guilt, the fact remains clearer to all of us

07:19.138 --> 07:21.481
We have all missed that mark.

07:21.641 --> 07:23.223
We are all guilty.

07:24.464 --> 07:30.832
Today we are watching protesters in the streets calling for justice and rioters tearing down statues.

07:31.473 --> 07:34.196
And they haven't stopped at Confederate memorials.

07:35.478 --> 07:42.867
They have torn down statues of Union soldiers, Christian saints, abolitionists, and presidents.

07:42.887 --> 07:45.490
And they don't stop when these statues are torn down.

07:46.551 --> 07:47.432
They deface them.

07:48.113 --> 07:49.074
They dismember them.

07:49.474 --> 07:50.135
They burn them.

07:50.636 --> 08:01.490
In the online world, we see similar behavior when mobs find someone who represents everything bad in their view, and they seek to destroy their lives publicly and painfully.

08:02.291 --> 08:10.802
When I see all this, I see nothing but people racked with guilt, looking for a symbolic scapegoat.

08:10.822 --> 08:14.066
If the tale is old as recorded human history.

08:14.594 --> 08:19.861
A perfect example I see of this is the Teddy Roosevelt statue in front of the Museum of Natural History.

08:21.022 --> 08:34.419
The ironic thing is that the statue, seen as a symbol of racism, is standing in front of the Museum of Natural History which was the intellectual center of eugenics and scientific racism in America in the early 20th century.

08:35.260 --> 08:39.285
Its legacy, in many ways, still survives today in the scientific community.

08:39.725 --> 08:43.570
If these people were consistent, they would tear the whole building down.

08:44.002 --> 08:52.134
The scientists and thinkers still living who are responsible for erasing that history and for that line of thinking would come forward and repent.

08:53.016 --> 08:53.997
That's not gonna happen.

08:55.239 --> 09:03.492
We all want justice, but we'd rather see that justice poured out on a scapegoat than turned against ourselves.

09:04.453 --> 09:12.786
Every one of the protesters and rioters and everyone else, you and me, has had hatred and anger in our hearts before.

09:12.962 --> 09:19.571
We all have the same core flaw that fueled racism 200 years ago and still fuels it today.

09:20.192 --> 09:25.860
But it's easier to tear down a statue than to address the sin in your own heart.

09:25.880 --> 09:40.480
Whether it be a statue, a building, or an online personality, I see people clawing at symbols, tearing down more and more in vain hope that it will banish evil from our shores, that it will assuage the guilt in our hearts.

09:41.281 --> 09:41.682
It won't.

09:42.082 --> 09:44.806
That guilt and shame will never be satisfied this way.

09:45.567 --> 09:49.011
That's why they won't stop until it's all torn down.

09:50.093 --> 09:50.934
So what's the good news?

09:52.376 --> 10:01.047
Well, the good news is that this ancient scapegoat was indeed symbolic, but it was symbolizing something very real.

10:01.888 --> 10:09.138
There was one who came, who took the sins of the world on himself and descended into Azazel.

10:09.602 --> 10:12.045
Only this wasn't a bowl or a sheep or a goat.

10:12.486 --> 10:16.210
It was God Himself who became a man in the form of Jesus.

10:17.151 --> 10:19.534
The sacrifice to end all sacrifices.

10:20.195 --> 10:22.678
The scapegoat to end all scapegoats.

10:23.559 --> 10:29.747
And if not for His sacrifice on the cross, we would all be desperately clawing at statues.

10:30.588 --> 10:35.874
And that's what we need to remember when we see the unwashed masses behaving badly.

10:36.956 --> 10:38.898
These are people without a shepherd.

10:39.010 --> 10:41.092
guilty consciences without a savior.

10:41.773 --> 10:44.015
Following a religion without grace.

10:44.976 --> 10:48.259
Following a mortal, impotent false god without hope.

10:49.220 --> 10:51.322
Let us be moved with compassion.

10:52.062 --> 10:53.844
Let us bring them the gospel.

10:54.725 --> 10:57.768
Because something happens when we have been forgiven much.

10:58.789 --> 11:06.276
It helps us to extend grace to our neighbors, to our political opponents, even our racist ancestors.

11:07.317 --> 11:08.818
We have good news to tell.

11:09.794 --> 11:25.330
News that you and me and the statue destroyers need to hear.

